external_knowledge:
- 'top 3 most coveted treasures' refers to the loot items with the highest total quantity collected by players for each character class;
- 'heroic class' refers to character classes in the game;
- 'most engaging game version' refers to the game version with a player engagement statistic value greater than 0.5, with the latest version chosen if multiple versions meet this condition;
- 'total spoils collected by players' refers to the total quantity of loot items collected by players for each character class.

External knowledge:
- "heroes who answered the call to adventure" refers to players who are active (i.e., `is_active = 1`);
- "most cherished" implies the loot item with the largest total quantity collected by active players.

sql:
SELECT AVG(drop_rate) AS average_drop_rate
FROM character_loot
WHERE class_id = (SELECT class_id FROM character_classes WHERE class_name = 'Hunter');

SELECT loot_id, AVG(loot_quantity) AS avg_loot_quantity
FROM player_loot
GROUP BY loot_id;

SELECT class_name
FROM character_classes
WHERE is_active = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS active_class_count
FROM character_classes
WHERE is_active = 1;

SELECT loot_name
FROM loot
WHERE loot_rarity = 'epic';

SELECT SUM(loot_quantity) AS total_loot_quantity
FROM player_loot
WHERE loot_id = 1;

SELECT SUM(loot_quantity) AS total_loot
FROM player_loot
WHERE player_id = 1;
